HEADWORD: Bookholder
<hw>Book"hold`er</hw> <pr>(b⟦oocr⟧k"h⟦omac⟧ld`⟦etil⟧r)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A prompter at a theater.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Beau. & Fl.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A support for a book, holding it open, while one
reads or copies from it.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Booking clerk</ent>⟦br⟧
